 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W2-001: Implement is_causal_ancestor(store, tx1, tx2) and wire into conflict detection. PROBLEM: Zero matches for 'causally_independent' or 'causal_ancestor' in entire kernel. resolution.rs:225-238 has_conflict() does not check causal independence — condition 6 of INV-RESOLUTION-004. Sequential single-agent updates to same (entity,attribute) are incorrectly flagged as conflicts when they are causal (each new assertion causally follows the previous). In multi-agent scenarios, legitimate causal chains (A writes, B reads A and updates) will be misclassified as concurrent conflicts. SOLUTION: (1) Implement is_causal_ancestor(store, tx1, tx2) -> bool via BFS over :tx/causal-predecessors graph. (2) Define causally_independent(store, tx1, tx2) = \\!is_causal_ancestor(store, tx1, tx2) && \\!is_causal_ancestor(store, tx2, tx1). (3) Wire into has_conflict() as condition 6: only flag conflict if assertions are causally independent. (4) Also add condition 5: check schema.cardinality(attr) == One (currently checks resolution mode instead of cardinality). VERIFICATION: (1) Unit test: two sequential assertions by same agent are NOT conflicts. (2) Unit test: two concurrent assertions by different agents with no causal link ARE conflicts. (3) proptest: for any DAG of transactions, causally_independent is symmetric and irreflexive. (4) Stateright model: conflict detection sound under all reachable states. DEPENDS-ON: None (leaf task). BLOCKS: W2-007 (conflict predicate accuracy affects Phi)."
